java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible, javax.swing.RootPaneContainer, javax.swing.WindowConstants
public class LineAttributeDialog
extends javax.swing.JDialog

Edits a LineAttribute. This dialog does not make a copy of the attribute so changes "Applied" will cause sgt to redraw the plot using the new properties unless batching has been turned on.

Example of LineAttributeDialog use: 

 public void editLineAttribute(LineAttribute attr) {
   LineAttributeDialog lad = new LineAttributeDialog();
   lad.setLineAttribute(attr);
   lad.setVisible(true);
 }
